{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"htmlAst":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Altair_8800"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Altair 8800"}]},{"type":"text","value":" was a\nbuild-it-yourself home computer kit released in 1975. The Altair was basically\nthe first personal computer, though it predated the advent of that term by\nseveral years. It is Adam (or Eve) to every Dell, HP, or Macbook out there."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"comment","value":"more"},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Some people thought it'd be awesome to write an emulator for the Z80—a\nprocessor closely related to the Altair's Intel 8080—and then thought it needed\na simulation of the Altair's control panel on top of it. So if you've ever\nwondered what it was like to use a computer in 1975, you can run the Altair on\nyour Macbook:"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"img","properties":{"src":"https://www.autometer.de/unix4fun/z80pack/altair.png","alt":"Altair 8800"},"children":[]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h3","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Installing it"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"You can download Z80 pack from the FTP server available\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"http://www.autometer.de/unix4fun/z80pack/ftp/"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"here"}]},{"type":"text","value":". You're looking for the\nlatest Z80 pack release, something like "},{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{"className":["language-text"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"z80pack-1.26.tgz"}]},{"type":"text","value":"."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"First unpack the file:"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"div","properties":{"className":["gatsby-highlight"],"dataLanguage":"text"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"pre","properties":{"className":["language-text"]},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{"className":["language-text"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"$ tar -xvf z80pack-1.26.tgz"}]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Move into the unpacked directory:"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"div","properties":{"className":["gatsby-highlight"],"dataLanguage":"text"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"pre","properties":{"className":["language-text"]},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{"className":["language-text"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"$ cd z80pack-1.26"}]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The control panel simulation is based on a library called "},{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{"className":["language-text"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"frontpanel"}]},{"type":"text","value":". You'll\nhave to compile that library first. If you move into the "},{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{"className":["language-text"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"frontpanel"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\ndirectory, you will find a "},{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{"className":["language-text"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"README"}]},{"type":"text","value":" file listing the libraries own\ndependencies. Your experience here will almost certainly differ from mine, but\nperhaps my travails will be illustrative. I had the dependencies installed, but\nvia "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"http://brew.sh/"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Homebrew"}]},{"type":"text","value":". To get the library to compile I just had to\nmake sure that "},{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{"className":["language-text"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"/usr/local/include"}]},{"type":"text","value":" was added to Clang's include path in\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{"className":["language-text"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Makefile.osx"}]},{"type":"text","value":"."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"If you've satisfied the dependencies, you should be able to compile the library\n(we're now in "},{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{"className":["language-text"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"z80pack-1.26/frontpanel"}]},{"type":"text","value":":"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"div","properties":{"className":["gatsby-highlight"],"dataLanguage":"text"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"pre","properties":{"className":["language-text"]},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{"className":["language-text"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"$ make -f Makefile.osx ...\n$ make -f Makefile.osx clean"}]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"You should end up with "},{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{"className":["language-text"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"libfrontpanel.so"}]},{"type":"text","value":". I copied this to "},{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{"className":["language-text"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"/usr/local/lib"}]},{"type":"text","value":"."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The Altair simulator is under "},{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{"className":["language-text"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"z80pack-1.26/altairsim"}]},{"type":"text","value":". You now need to compile\nthe simulator itself. Move into "},{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{"className":["language-text"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"z80pack-1.26/altairsim/srcsim"}]},{"type":"text","value":" and run "},{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{"className":["language-text"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"make"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\nonce more:"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"div","properties":{"className":["gatsby-highlight"],"dataLanguage":"text"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"pre","properties":{"className":["language-text"]},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{"className":["language-text"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"$ make -f Makefile.osx ...\n$ make -f Makefile.osx clean"}]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"That process will create an executable called "},{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{"className":["language-text"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"altairsim"}]},{"type":"text","value":" one level up in\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{"className":["language-text"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"z80pack-1.26/altairsim"}]},{"type":"text","value":". Run that executable and you should see that iconic\nAltair control panel!"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"And if you really want to nerd out, read through the original "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"http://www.classiccmp.org/dunfield/altair/d/88opman.pdf"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Altair\nmanual"}]},{"type":"text","value":"."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"hr","properties":{},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{"style":"color:#5f5f5f;font-size:16px;font-style: italic;padding-top:2em;text-align:center"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\noriginally posted at "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://twobithistory.org"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"two bit history"}]},{"type":"text","value":" under \n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"CC BY-SA 4.0"}]},{"type":"text","value":" by "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"http://sinclairtarget.com"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Sinclair Target"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"}]}],"data":{"quirksMode":false}},"frontmatter":{"title":"Simulating the Altair","author":{"name":"Sinclair Target"},"date":"02 December 2017"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/blog/series/2bithistory/simulating-the-altair/"}}